WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.637
- Merry Christmas.

00:00:01.637 --> 00:00:04.131
Merry Christmas movie house.

00:00:04.131 --> 00:00:05.936
Oh, that's my house.

00:00:05.936 --> 00:00:07.851
Merry Christmas.

00:00:07.851 --> 00:00:08.768
Mary, Mary.

00:00:09.762 --> 00:00:11.345
There you are Mary.

00:00:12.340 --> 00:00:13.616
- George, George it's wonderful.

00:00:13.616 --> 00:00:14.762
It's wonderful Mary.

00:00:14.762 --> 00:00:15.597
She did it.

00:00:15.597 --> 00:00:17.829
She told some people you were in trouble

00:00:17.829 --> 00:00:19.987
and she scattered all over town

00:00:19.987 --> 00:00:21.045
and collected all the money.

00:00:21.045 --> 00:00:22.625
You got everything you need.

00:00:22.625 --> 00:00:24.333
It's wonderful, George.

00:00:24.333 --> 00:00:26.995
- To George Bailey, the
richest man in town.

00:00:26.995 --> 00:00:30.714
♪Should old acquaintance be forgot ♪

00:00:30.714 --> 00:00:34.117
♪ And never brought to mind ♪

00:00:34.117 --> 00:00:35.193
- Hang on a minute.

00:00:35.193 --> 00:00:36.030
Wait a second.

00:00:36.030 --> 00:00:37.391
Wait a second.

00:00:37.391 --> 00:00:39.891
This is only like 413 dollars.

00:00:40.835 --> 00:00:42.794
- Well, how much money
do you need, George?

00:00:42.794 --> 00:00:44.059
- 8000 dollars.

00:00:44.059 --> 00:00:45.973
(crowd grumbles)

00:00:45.973 --> 00:00:48.292
- Well, surely we can raise enough.

00:00:48.292 --> 00:00:50.000
How about everyone gives another dollar.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:51.902
- [Crowd] Yes, that's a great idea.

00:00:51.902 --> 00:00:52.735
- Hang on.

00:00:52.735 --> 00:00:53.568
Hey, hang on.

00:00:53.568 --> 00:00:55.754
that's only like 17 more dollars.

00:00:55.754 --> 00:00:56.719
- Well, hooray.

00:00:56.719 --> 00:00:57.928
We're almost there.

00:00:57.928 --> 00:00:58.961
- [Crowd] Hooray.

00:00:58.961 --> 00:00:59.794
- Hip hip.

00:00:59.794 --> 00:01:02.275
♪ Should old acquaintance
be forgot and never ♪

00:01:02.275 --> 00:01:03.108
- Shut up.

00:01:03.108 --> 00:01:04.185
Shut up.

00:01:04.185 --> 00:01:05.018
Shut up.

00:01:05.018 --> 00:01:05.851
- Alright.

00:01:05.851 --> 00:01:07.925
- Come on, couldn't you
just give a little more.

00:01:07.925 --> 00:01:10.418
- Well, I have this 10 dollar bill.

00:01:10.418 --> 00:01:11.412
- [Crowd] Ohhhhh.

00:01:11.412 --> 00:01:12.263
- That's more like it.

00:01:12.263 --> 00:01:13.096
Thank you Mila.

00:01:13.096 --> 00:01:15.492
I'll just take 6 singles
back and that's almost

00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:17.856
8000 dollars on the nose.

00:01:17.856 --> 00:01:19.425
(crowd cheering)

00:01:19.425 --> 00:01:20.894
- Stop taking my money.

00:01:20.894 --> 00:01:22.120
(mila crying)

00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:23.081
- Look what you've done.

00:01:23.081 --> 00:01:25.112
- You can't make change with this money.

00:01:25.112 --> 00:01:26.024
- I have an idea.

00:01:26.024 --> 00:01:27.479
Let's have a bake sale.

00:01:27.479 --> 00:01:30.722
We'll make teeny, tiny
pies, charge 10 cents a pie.

00:01:30.722 --> 00:01:33.336
Heck, I bet we could make 100 pies even.

00:01:33.336 --> 00:01:34.330
I love that.

00:01:34.330 --> 00:01:35.741
- That's only 10 dollars.

00:01:35.741 --> 00:01:36.617
- Well, how do you figure?

00:01:36.617 --> 00:01:37.569
- Math.

00:01:37.569 --> 00:01:40.065
Do you people know how money works?

00:01:40.065 --> 00:01:43.193
- Yes, one, two, three, four, five six.

00:01:43.193 --> 00:01:44.162
- There you go.

00:01:44.162 --> 00:01:45.765
- This is a plastic nickel.

00:01:45.765 --> 00:01:46.787
- I brought the nickels.

00:01:46.787 --> 00:01:47.902
- I don't even know you.

00:01:47.902 --> 00:01:48.735
- I'm Cecil.

00:01:48.735 --> 00:01:49.568
- That's Cecil.

00:01:49.568 --> 00:01:50.401
- Who? - Cecil

00:01:50.401 --> 00:01:51.234
- George, we've met.

00:01:51.234 --> 00:01:52.781
- You're a stranger to me.

00:01:52.781 --> 00:01:53.957
- George, why don't we have Mary sell

00:01:53.957 --> 00:01:56.485
some of her pretty, pretty hair?

00:01:56.485 --> 00:01:59.036
- I... I'm not gonna do that.

00:01:59.036 --> 00:02:00.067
- Quiet everybody.

00:02:00.067 --> 00:02:01.883
A telegram from your rich friend, Sam.

00:02:01.883 --> 00:02:02.890
- [Crowd] Ohhhh.

00:02:02.890 --> 00:02:03.723
- A telegram.

00:02:03.723 --> 00:02:04.763
- George, stop.

00:02:04.763 --> 00:02:06.330
My office is instructed to advance you

00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:08.080
up to 25,000 dollars.

00:02:09.151 --> 00:02:09.984
- [Crowd] Ohhhh.

00:02:09.984 --> 00:02:12.106
- Stop, hee haw and merry Christmas.

00:02:12.106 --> 00:02:13.227
- [Crowd] Awwwwww

00:02:13.227 --> 00:02:14.333
- A hee haw indeed.

00:02:14.333 --> 00:02:17.586
♪ Should old acquaintance be forgot. ♪

00:02:17.586 --> 00:02:18.488
♪ (man barking) ♪

00:02:18.488 --> 00:02:19.321
- Hold on.

00:02:19.321 --> 00:02:20.154
Hold on.

00:02:20.154 --> 00:02:20.987
Sorry.

00:02:20.987 --> 00:02:21.820
There's more.

00:02:21.820 --> 00:02:23.267
I just need you to wait 12 weeks

00:02:23.267 --> 00:02:24.761
for a check to clear, stop.

00:02:24.761 --> 00:02:26.574
Hee haw and merry Christmas.

00:02:26.574 --> 00:02:27.793
- [Mila] Hee haw indeed.

00:02:27.793 --> 00:02:28.958
- 12 weeks.

00:02:28.958 --> 00:02:29.791
12 weeks.

00:02:30.820 --> 00:02:32.170
I'm going to jail tonight.

00:02:32.170 --> 00:02:33.003
- Judge.

00:02:33.003 --> 00:02:34.385
- I'll pay 400 dollars for her hair,

00:02:34.385 --> 00:02:36.852
but that's twice as much
as I usually pay for hair.

00:02:36.852 --> 00:02:37.685
- What's with the hair.

00:02:37.685 --> 00:02:38.518
- It's Christmas.

00:02:38.518 --> 00:02:40.275
We all can do whatever we like.

00:02:40.275 --> 00:02:41.179
- What do you do with it.

00:02:41.179 --> 00:02:42.596
- Sniff it and lick it.

00:02:42.596 --> 00:02:43.606
- Stop.

00:02:43.606 --> 00:02:45.753
Can't any of you small town idiots

00:02:45.753 --> 00:02:47.873
give me anything else?

00:02:47.873 --> 00:02:51.540
- Eh, ahem, I guess we
gotta arrest you now.

00:02:53.054 --> 00:02:53.887
(tightening of handcuffs)

00:02:53.887 --> 00:02:54.720
- [George] Alright.

00:02:54.720 --> 00:02:55.553
- [Policeman] Let's go.

00:02:55.553 --> 00:02:56.386
- [George] Ouch, ouch.

00:02:56.386 --> 00:02:57.219
[Mary] Oh George.

00:02:57.219 --> 00:02:58.596
- It's in between my fingers.

00:02:58.596 --> 00:03:00.041
[Crowd] Bye George.

00:03:00.041 --> 00:03:00.899
- Merry Christmas George.

00:03:00.899 --> 00:03:02.248
- [Crowd] Merry Christmas George.

00:03:02.248 --> 00:03:03.873
[Cecil] Nice to meet you.

00:03:03.873 --> 00:03:04.706
- Hee haw.

00:03:05.690 --> 00:03:06.523
- I guess we should just take back

00:03:06.523 --> 00:03:07.810
our money, right, that's cool.

00:03:07.810 --> 00:03:08.643
Yeah.

00:03:09.598 --> 00:03:11.330
- [Crowd] Yes.

00:03:11.330 --> 00:03:14.238
♪ Should old acquaintance be forgot. ♪

00:03:14.238 --> 00:03:17.738
(closing orchestra music)

00:03:20.299 --> 00:03:22.183
- Clarence, my guardian angel.

00:03:22.183 --> 00:03:24.074
- Why, hear you go George.

00:03:24.074 --> 00:03:25.844
- Wha... what is that?

00:03:25.844 --> 00:03:28.408
- In heaven, we use clouds as money.

00:03:28.408 --> 00:03:31.563
- Clouds are worth nothing to me Clarence.

00:03:31.563 --> 00:03:33.960
I need 8000 dollars.

00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:35.500
- 8 grand, what?

00:03:35.500 --> 00:03:37.083
- That's what I was trying to tell you

00:03:37.083 --> 00:03:39.503
on the bridge you dumb angel.

